00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:16,300
Dear, this one.

101
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:21,600
Let me tell you. His family is so rich that two generations can enjoy the wealth.

102
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,820
What's so great about having money?

103
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:26,920
Our Nuan Nuan doesn't lack money.

104
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:31,120
<i>Then this one, born to a family of doctors and has a doctorate degree.</i>

105
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,380
Right, a family of doctors and nurses.

106
00:08:33,380 --> 00:08:35,900
Future medical treatments and injections can be guaranteed.

107
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,320
Right.

108
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:40,840
My daughter isn't marrying to get medical treatment!

109
00:08:42,540 --> 00:08:46,720
Dear, what do you think of that young man outside?

110
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,800
I don't think much of him.

111
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:59,060
He's so handsome, and you're still picky.

112
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:02,120
Our Nuan Nuan doesn't just value looks.

113
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,540
I'll tell you something.

114
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:06,680
When choosing a son-in-law, you must value his character.

115
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:10,780
He has to be good to my daughter, truly love my daughter,

116
00:09:11,380 --> 00:09:14,960
<i>and not hide anything from her.</i>

117
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:18,580
He must be sincere to my daughter.

118
00:09:18,580 --> 00:09:21,440
In short, if he sincerely loves my daughter,

119
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:24,180
I can be a satisfied mother-in-law.

120
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:28,480
If he openly or secretly bullies my daughter,

121
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:32,340
I will teach him a lesson as Mother-in-law.

122
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:38,720
What does he do?

123
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,500
He runs a seafood business at home.

124
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:43,300
Here's your water. Are you from out of town?

125
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,600
Uncle.

126
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:51,140
If you don't mind, would you join me for a drink later?

127
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:53,300
But I drove here.

128
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:55,920
What does it matter? If you get drunk, stay here.

129
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:58,160
Wait, I'll get the wine.

130
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,000
I prepared in a rush.

131
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,860
I haven't made any good dishes to serve you.

132
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:13,200
It's already very good.

133
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,900
No problem, there's more.

134
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,500
Children's mother (Dear).

135
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,560
I'm coming, coming.

136
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:20,040
What are you shouting for?

137
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:22,800
It's so cold, yet you're making him drink. So silly.

138
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,880
Drink if you want. Why do I have to serve you?

139
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:29,040
Here's your squirrel-shaped mandarin fish and salted duck.

140
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,620
My wife is the best. My wife is the best.

141
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:35,140
You dare to drink.

142
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:36,740
You're even drinking cold wine on a cold day.

143
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,980
Wait, I'll warm it for you.

144
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,100
- Thank you, Auntie.
- Okay, okay.

145
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,720
Don't mind what she said.

146
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:52,720
She's always like this. Her words are harsh, but her heart is soft.

147
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,540
She doesn't display affection,

148
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:58,240
but just keeps it in her heart for a lifetime.

149
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,400
Auntie is so nice.

150
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,080
Is that so?

151
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:10,760
Actually, let me tell you; all parents are the same.

152
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:15,160
At first, they hope their children will be successful.

153
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:19,820
Later on, they hope their children can have a better life.

154
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:24,320
In the end, they all hope their children can be happy.

155
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:29,140
Sometimes, when they blame you or don't understand you,

156
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:33,040
their love for you makes them emotional.

157
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:38,480
They're afraid that you'll make the same mistakes

158
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:41,768
that they did before.

159
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:45,200
So from the moment you were born,

160
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:48,060
they've been carefully protecting you.

161
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:50,020
When you grow up,

162
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:54,420
they hope you can have a better life than they did.

163
00:11:56,040 --> 00:12:00,480
In this world, parents love their child.

164
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:05,360
No parents want to become enemies with their child.

165
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:08,460
When they hit or scold you,

166
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:12,040
the ones who hurt most are the parents.

167
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:19,500
I have two children about your age.

168
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:23,040
I won't discuss my son. That rascal does whatever he wants.

169
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:26,040
He would dare to do anything.

170
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:28,200
But my daughter…

171
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:32,260
Do you want to hear about my daughter?

172
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:34,960
I want to hear.

173
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:41,200
My daughter has been a very lovely child since childhood.

174
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:46,260
She was chubby, fair and charming.

175
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:50,980
But she always had bad luck.

176
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:57,560
However, no matter what misfortunes occur,

177
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:01,920
she is always optimistic and kind.

178
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:06,940
Actually, I never thought my daughter was unlucky.

179
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:11,020
Even though some setbacks and difficulties are in her life,

180
00:13:11,020 --> 00:13:16,100
I believe she can use her wisdom, kindness, and innocence

181
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:19,260
to resolve these issues one by one.

182
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:24,700
In fact, no one in this world has everything go well.

183
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:29,740
Likewise, no one is always at the bottom of the heap.

184
00:13:29,740 --> 00:13:34,340
What distinguishes people is how you respond to issues.

185
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:36,340
Some people pull themselves together

186
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:39,600
to have a better life.

187
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,820
But some people crumble.

188
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:48,200
For such people, none of us can help them, right?

189
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,310
So

190
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:56,000
I hope you can be like her. Pull yourself together and start over.

191
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:58,836
Here.

192
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,040
Here, eat.

193
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:11,100
Don't just chat.

194
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:13,620
Stay here tonight.

195
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,664
How does it taste?

196
00:14:35,970 --> 00:14:37,910
<i>[Honorary Credential]
[National (VHS)]</i>

197
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:42,020
There are so many comic books.

198
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:44,000
She really didn't lie to me.

199
00:15:17,148 --> 00:15:21,272
Why does it feel like I've seen her somewhere?

200
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:25,230
<i>[Zhao Nuan Nuan, aged 9, commemoration of hospital discharge]</i>

201
00:15:44,734 --> 00:15:46,934
<i>Nuan Nuan.</i>

202
00:15:47,914 --> 00:15:50,354
<i>Why are you over here again?</i>

203
00:15:50,354 --> 00:15:52,714
<i>Did you take your medicine and get your injection?</i>

204
00:15:52,714 --> 00:15:56,794
<i>You're about to get your tonsillectomy in a few days. You can't catch a cold. Come on.</i>

205
