221
00:17:02,014 --> 00:17:06,034
This won't do. You should talk to each other.

222
00:17:06,034 --> 00:17:08,954
I know what he's thinking.

223
00:17:10,734 --> 00:17:14,214
He must think that I did it on purpose,

224
00:17:14,214 --> 00:17:16,334
and he must blame me.

225
00:17:16,334 --> 00:17:20,754
He thought that I deliberately took him to the porridge shop to see his mother.

226
00:17:22,054 --> 00:17:25,254
But I really didn't know about it.

227
00:17:27,734 --> 00:17:33,372
I also didn't know he had so much pain in his past.

228
00:17:33,414 --> 00:17:35,774
In fact, I don't blame him.

229
00:17:36,454 --> 00:17:38,434
It's all my fault.

230
00:17:38,434 --> 00:17:41,554
I've never tried to understand him.

231
00:17:42,594 --> 00:17:47,614
I've never known what he truly wants.

232
00:17:47,614 --> 00:17:52,934
All I knew was to pursue him desperately, forcing him to accept me.

233
00:17:54,354 --> 00:17:59,234
If I had known our relationship was doomed to end,

234
00:17:59,234 --> 00:18:02,614
then it would have been better not to start.

235
00:18:02,614 --> 00:18:04,094
Mi Mi.

236
00:18:06,154 --> 00:18:08,994
My mother called me.

237
00:18:09,654 --> 00:18:11,454
I might…

238
00:18:11,454 --> 00:18:13,754
I might have to return to USA soon.

239
00:18:13,754 --> 00:18:15,374
So soon?

240
00:18:15,374 --> 00:18:18,214
Just like Senior Nan said,

241
00:18:19,634 --> 00:18:23,034
we will pretend we've never met.

242
00:18:25,834 --> 00:18:29,174
But I really like him!

243
00:18:30,154 --> 00:18:34,334
I really, really like Senior Nan.

244
00:18:35,554 --> 00:18:37,116
I don't want to leave.

245
